  "prompt": "Can Google help me track my lost Android phone by the IMEI number?",
  "response": "Google does not directly allow you to track a lost Android phone using the IMEI number. However, there are other methods you can use to locate your lost device through Google's services. \n\nOne of the most effective tools is the \"Find My Device\" feature, which you can access through the following steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Find My Device website:** Visit https://www.google.com/android/find or download the \"Find My Device\" app from the Google Play Store on another Android device.\n\n2. **Sign in:** Log in with the Google account that is associated with the lost phone.\n\n3. **Locate your device:** Once signed in, you should be able to see your device on a map, if it's turned on and has an active internet connection. You can also ring the device, lock it, or erase its data remotely.\n\nThe IMEI number itself is more useful for reporting your lost device to your carrier or the police. Your carrier may be able to use the IMEI number to block the device from being used on their network, and law enforcement can use it to track or identify the device if it is recovered.\n\nIf your phone is turned off or not connected to the internet, the \"Find My Device\" feature won't be able to provide real-time location updates, but it can still offer the last known location where the device was connected.",
